Greenbury Secondary School has broken records for the matric year 2015 when three of their learners featured in the top 10 in KZN. According to Umalusi, the quality assurer body for matric examinations, nearly 800 000 learners sat for National Senior Certificate exams. This is 123 000 more than 2014. Despite a drop in the Matric 2015 pass rate, an upbeat Angie Motshekga, praised learners for remembering that &#8220;Basic education was not a sprint.&#8221;